        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(telegram): preserve persistent rich message line breaks",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nFixes #95409.\n\nTelegram persistent rich messages can collapse ordinary final-answer line breaks when `richMessages` is enabled. The plain `sendMessage` path preserves a normal assistant reply like:\n\n```text\n第一行\n第二行\n第三行\n```\n\nbut the Bot API 10.1 persistent rich-message path sends `rich_message.html`, where literal text-node `\\n` is not a reliable visual line break. This makes structured replies look compressed even though the account explicitly opted into rich messages.\n\nThis PR fixes the supported persistent rich-message path only. It does **not** use `sendRichMessageDraft`, does not change native draft streaming behavior, and does not introduce an extra final message bubble.\n\n## Summary\n\n- Preserve text-node line breaks during Telegram rich HTML preparation.\n- Convert ordinary non-whitespace text-node `\\n` to `<br>` before sending `rich_message.html`.\n- Convert standalone newline separators between formatted inline rich HTML nodes, e.g. `<b>one</b>\\n<a>two</a>`, to `<br>`.\n- Leave pure structural whitespace between block/container tags unchanged, including pretty-printed rich tables.\n- Leave newlines inside `<pre>`, `<code>`, `<tg-math>`, and `<tg-math-block>` literal.\n- Add regression tests for rich final-message line breaks, inline formatted separators, preformatted/code blocks, math blocks, and pretty-printed rich tables.\n\n## Implementation Notes\n\nThe previous preparation path sanitized rich HTML and enforced Telegram's nesting limit:\n\n```ts\nfunction prepareTelegramRichHtml(html: string): string {\n  return limitTelegramRichHtmlNesting(sanitizeTelegramRichHtml(html), TELEGRAM_RICH_NESTING_LIMIT);\n}\n```\n\nThe new helper runs after sanitization and before nesting-limit enforcement. It walks HTML tags, tracks protected rich text regions, and materializes newlines only where Telegram Rich Messages need explicit `<br>` separators. That keeps existing HTML structure and code/preformatted/math content stable while making normal assistant text readable in persistent rich Telegram messages.\n\n## Evidence\n\nCandidate head verified: `c96b581991c1224bbf4a57606080dc92863f5961`.\n\nSource and diff checks:\n\n```text\ngit diff --check\n# passed\n\ngit diff -- extensions/telegram/src | grep -q 'sendRichMessageDraft'\n# no sendRichMessageDraft changes\n```\n\nRegression coverage added:\n\n- `preserves plain line breaks in native rich final messages`\n- `preserves line breaks between formatted inline rich HTML nodes`\n- `keeps preformatted rich HTML newlines literal`\n- `keeps math rich HTML newlines literal`\n- `keeps pretty-printed rich table structure without break tags`\n\nDirect Telegram Bot API proof passed for current candidate head `c96b581991c1224bbf4a57606080dc92863f5961` using `sendRichMessage` with sanitized artifacts `summary.md`, `request.sanitized.json`, and `response.sanitized.json`:\n\n- `getMe`: HTTP 200, `ok: true`, bot username present.\n- `sendRichMessage`: HTTP 200, `ok: true`, result contains `has_rich_message: true`.\n- Request operation: `sendRichMessage`.\n- Request endpoint: `https://api.telegram.org/bot[REDACTED]/sendRichMessage`.\n- Request target: `chat_id: \"[REDACTED_CHAT]\"`.\n- `inlineSeparatorMaterialized`: `true` (`</b><br><a href=\"https://example.com\">`).\n- `plainLineBreaksMaterialized`: `true` (`plain-one<br>plain-two`).\n- `codeLineBreakLiteral`: `true` (`<pre><code>code-one\\ncode-two</code></pre>` remains literal).\n- `mathLineBreakLiteral`: `true` (`<tg-math>x\\ny</tg-math>` remains literal).\n- `native draft used`: `false`; the proof did not use `sendRichMessageDraft`.\n\nDirect Telegram Bot API proof also passed for candidate head `208901cf809721209b81a75fb41baf63c14b62a8` using a direct `getMe` + `sendRichMessage` Bot API path with sanitized artifacts `summary.md`, `request.sanitized.json`, and `response.sanitized.json`:\n\n- `getMe`: HTTP 200, `ok: true`, bot username present.\n- `sendRichMessage`: HTTP 200, `ok: true`, result contains `has_rich_message: true`.\n- Request operation: `sendRichMessage`.\n- Request endpoint: `https://api.telegram.org/bot[REDACTED]/sendRichMessage`.\n- Request target: `chat_id: \"[REDACTED_CHAT]\"`.\n- `inlineSeparatorMaterialized`: `true` (`</b><br><a href=\"https://example.com\">`).\n- `plainLineBreaksMaterialized`: `true` (`plain-one<br>plain-two`).\n- `codeLineBreakLiteral`: `true` (`<pre><code>code-one\\ncode-two</code></pre>` remains literal).\n- `mathLineBreakLiteral`: `true` (`<tg-math>x\\ny</tg-math>` remains literal).\n- `native draft used`: `false`; the proof did not use `sendRichMessageDraft`.\n\nNo local build was run or used as proof for this PR.\n\n## Risk / Rollback\n\nRisk is limited to Telegram accounts that opted into rich messages. The change is conservative because it only affects text nodes that contain non-whitespace content and avoids preformatted/code/math blocks and supported rich table/container structure.\n\nRollback: revert this PR to return rich HTML preparation to sanitize + nesting limit only.\n\n",
